The match fixing cloud has been hovering around Kenyan football and is said to be spreading its tentacles in the football clubs because of the betting craze and poor and structured pay for footballers in the country.Former Mathare United defender George Owino was banned by FIFA from football related matters for 10 years after he was found guilty of an attempt to try and manipulate international matches. A Ugandan national will on Monday appear before a Kisumu Court where he will face immigration and corruption related charges for attempting to fix a Betking Premier league match.  
The foreigner was on Saturday arrested at a Kisumu hotel trying to bribe four Western Stima FC players and the team manager in order to lose Sunday's Premier league fixture against KCB.



