Mr Ken Okaka, the communications officer at FKF, confirmed having received the information from Mr Jobita and said they had forwarded the same to the world football governing body FIFA.
The match fixing cloud has been hovering around Kenyan football and is said to be spreading its tentacles in the football clubs because of the betting craze and poor and structured pay for footballers in the country.
Former Mathare United defender George Owino was banned by FIFA from football related matters for 10 years after he was found guilty of an attempt to try and manipulate international matches. Locals are living in fear of more raids by the bandits, who are reported to be hiding in bushes. Party leader Raila Odinga has not stated whether he will run for the top seat but he is seen as the clear favourite. Benson Mutura, who lasted 28 days as Nairobi's acting governor, recounts his days at the helm of Kenya’s capital city.